Victor Oduor will hit a milestone this weekend when he takes charge of his 100th match after being named as the center referee for Saturday’s Kenya Cup final. Defending champions Kabras Sugar take on KCB in the 3.00 p.m kick off at the Kakamega showground The Ngecho Secondary School Librarian is a World Rugby Level 3 Accredited Match Official.  He has been the Secretary of Rift Valley Rugby Referees Society since 2014. He also serves on the Rugby Africa Match Officials panel, is a World Rugby Match Officials Educator as well as being the Kenya Rugby Union’s Regional Development Officer for the South Rift region. Oduor has officiated at the World Rugby Junior Trophy as well as various Rugby Africa continental fixtures. He will be assisted by Constant Cap and Duncan Kioko with Willy Ombisi serving as the match commissioner.